y, Cumberland, England":"Ireby, Cumbraland, England, United Kingdom","High Ireby, Cumberland, England":"High Ireby, Cumbraland, England, United Kingdom","Cumberland, England":"Cumbraland, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1317–Abt 1412":"1317–circa 1412","1317–1412":"1317–1412","1319–1362":"1319–1362","1355–1401":"1355–1401","1281–Male":"1281–Overleden","1285–Female":"1285–Overleden","8 February 1362":"8 februari 1362","1401":"1401","1412":"1412","1355":"1355","1285":"1285","1362":"1362","Abt 1412":"circa 1412","1281":"1281","1319":"1319","1317":"1317","Borthwick, Midlothian, Scotland":"Borthwick, Midlothian, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Ireby, Cumberland, England":"Ireby, Cumberland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","High Ireby, Cumberland, England":"High Ireby, Cumberland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1317–Abt 1412":"1317–about 1412","1317–1412":"1317–1412","1319–1362":"1319–1362","1355–1401":"1355–1401","1281–Male":"1281–Deceased","1285–Female":"1285–Deceased","8 February 1362":"8 February 1362","1401":"1401","1412":"1412","1355":"1355","1285":"1285","1362":"1362","Abt 1412":"about 1412","1281":"1281","1319":"1319","1317":"1317","Borthwick, Midlothian, Scotland":"Borthwick, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ireby, Cumberland, England":"Ireby, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom","High Ireby, Cumberland, England":"High Ireby, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Ireby","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Irby in Lincolnshire, Cheshire, and North Yorkshire, or Ireby (Cumberland and Lancashire), all named from Old Norse <i>Írabýr</i> ‘settlement of the Irish’. Compare   Ireton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ireton","meanings":["English: most probably a habitational name from Kirk Ireton (Derbyshire) or perhaps from Ireton Farm in Weston Underwood (Derbyshire), both named in Anglo-Scandinavian as <i>Íratūn</i> ‘settlement of the Irish’ or more likely ‘settlement of the Irishman’. The reference may be either to a Scandinavian Viking who had been in Ireland or to an Irishman who came to England with the Vikings. Occasionally the name may also derive from either of two places called Irton in North Yorkshire, of which Irton in Seamer parish is a more likely source than the lost Irton in Coxwold. Both the North Yorkshire places have the same etymologies as those above."]},{"name":"Erby","meanings":["English: variant of   Irby  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William De Ireby was born in 1317, in Cumberland, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Irby, was 36 and his mother, Agnes Kirkley, was 32. He had at least 1 son with Lady Catherine \"Baroness of Borthwick\" de le Haye. He died about 1412, in Ireby, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 96."},"et":{"1317–Abt 1412":"1317–umbes 1412","1317–1412":"1317–1412","1319–1362":"1319–1362","1355–1401":"1355–1401","1281–Male":"1281–Surnud","1285–Female":"1285–Surnud","8 February 1362":"8. veebruar 1362","1401":"1401","1412":"1412","1355":"1355","1285":"1285","1362":"1362","Abt 1412":"umbes 1412","1281":"1281","1319":"1319","1317":"1317","Borthwick, Midlothian, Scotland":"Borthwick, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ireby, Cumberland, England":"Ireby, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","High Ireby, Cumberland, England":"High Ireby, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1317–Abt 1412":"1317–noin 1412","1317–1412":"1317–1412","1319–1362":"1319–1362","1355–1401":"1355–1401","1281–Male":"1281–Kuollut","1285–Female":"1285–Kuollut","8 February 1362":"8. helmikuuta 1362","1401":"1401","1412":"1412","1355":"1355","1285":"1285","1362":"1362","Abt 1412":"noin 1412","1281":"1281","1319":"1319","1317":"1317","Borthwick, Midlothian, Scotland":"Borthwick, Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Ireby, Cumberland, England":"Ireby, Cumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","High Ireby, Cumberland, England":"High Ireby, Cumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1317–Abt 1412":"1317–environ 1412","1317–1412":"1317–1412","1319–13